    region strong-livelabs-sandbox-span-style-color-green-em-lite-em-span-strong (
        name: <strong>LiveLabs Sandbox <span style="color:green;"><em>Lite</em> </span> Request</strong>
        type: staticContent
        source {
            htmlCode:
                ```html
                A Sandbox Lite is a quick an easy way to create a Sandbox for your workshop. Instead of provisioning actual resources for the lab, a Sandbox Lite will spin up an environment in one of the LiveLabs tenancies with policies and quotas that will allow the USER to provision resources. <br><br>
                For the options below, specify if you would like the USER of your workshop to be able to spin up one of the noted resources. This DOES NOT CREATE any resources on the users behalf. This merely allows the user to create it themselves (with the exception of the VCN option, that option -- if checked -- will automatically provision a VCN for the user).
                <br>
                ```
        }
        layout {
            sequence: 30
            parentRegion: @request-a-livelabs-sandbox
            slot: regionBody
            startNewRow: false
            newColumn: false
        }
        appearance {
            template: @standard
            templateOptions: [
                #DEFAULT#
                t-Region--scrollBody
                margin-top-md
            ]
            renderComponents: belowContent
        }
    )

